<Node id="1"/>USA: Fortress to buy Don Galloway for $21 mln.<Node id="47"/>
<Node id="48"/>Fortress to buy Don Galloway for $21 mln.<Node id="89"/>
<Node id="90"/>VIENNA, Va. 1997-08-19<Node id="112"/>
<Node id="113"/>
<Node id="114"/>Fortress Group Inc said Tuesday it agreed to buy Don Galloway Homes Inc of Charlotte, N.C., for $21 million.<Node id="222"/>
<Node id="223"/>The home manufacturer said the acquisition, which it expects to close August 31, will add $0.06 a share to Fortress' earnings for the remainder of 1997.<Node id="375"/>
<Node id="376"/>On a pro-forma basis, Fortress projected Galloway to add $0.20 a share for the whole of 1997, assuming it had bought Galloway on January 1.  <Node id="517"/>
<Node id="518"/>An August 15 First Call consensus estimate of two analysts had put the company's earnings at $0.35 a share for the third quarter, $0.48 a share in the fourth quarter, and $1.14 for the full year.<Node id="713"/>
<Node id="714"/>Fortress said it will pay for Don Galloway $5 million in cash; $5 million in a short-term note; $6 million in newly-issued zero dividend convertible and redeemable preferred stock; and an earnout of up to $5 million, which it will pay through the year 2000.  <Node id="973"/>
<Node id="974"/>Fortress said Don Galloway posted a pre-tax profit of $7.8 million on gross revenues of $66 million (delivering 470 homes) for the fiscal year ended June 30. Don Galloway's backlog stood at 235 homes with a total value of $33 million as of June 30, Fortress added.<Node id="1238"/>
<Node id="1239"/>Fortress added it used the proceeds of a recent Lazard Freres Real Estate Investors LLC affiliate's investment in the company to finance the acquisition.<Node id="1392"/>
<Node id="1393"/>The home manufacturer announced August 15 Lazard affiliate Prometheus Homebuilders LLC agreed to invest $75 million in Fortress and considered investing up to $25 million more in 1999.<Node id="1577"/>
<Node id="1578"/>Fortress' stock rose 1/16 to 5-1/4 Tuesday morning.<Node id="1629"/>
